{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":949,"text":"I'd like to have you look at this pencil."},{"time":3550,"text":"It's a thing. It's a legal thing."},{"time":6407,"text":"And so are books you might have\nor the cars you own."},{"time":10319,"text":"They're all legal things."},{"time":12258,"text":"The great apes that you'll see behind me,"},{"time":15881,"text":"they too are legal things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19549,"text":"Now, I can do that to a legal thing."},{"time":23822,"text":"I can do whatever I want\nto my book or my car."},{"time":26631,"text":"These great apes, you'll see."},{"time":29533,"text":"The photographs are taken by a man\nnamed James Mollison"},{"time":33420,"text":"who wrote a book called\n\"James &amp; Other Apes.\""},{"time":36464,"text":"And he tells in his book\nhow every single one them,"},{"time":39227,"text":"almost every one of them, is an orphan"},{"time":41525,"text":"who saw his mother and father\ndie before his eyes."},{"time":46110,"text":"They're legal things."}]},{"cues":[{"time":47748,"text":"So for centuries, there's been\na great legal wall"},{"time":50441,"text":"that separates legal things\nfrom legal persons."},{"time":53785,"text":"On one hand, legal things\nare invisible to judges."},{"time":57570,"text":"They don't count in law."},{"time":59520,"text":"They don't have any legal rights."},{"time":61215,"text":"They don't have\nthe capacity for legal rights."},{"time":63699,"text":"They are the slaves."},{"time":65836,"text":"On the other side of that legal wall\nare the legal persons."},{"time":68660,"text":"Legal persons are very visible to judges."},{"time":71607,"text":"They count in law."},{"time":73312,"text":"They may have many rights."},{"time":75239,"text":"They have the capacity\nfor an infinite number of rights."},{"time":78142,"text":"And they're the masters."},{"time":81300,"text":"Right now, all nonhuman animals\nare legal things."},{"time":85779,"text":"All human beings are legal persons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":88660,"text":"But being human and being a legal person"},{"time":91469,"text":"has never been, and is not today,\nsynonymous with a legal person."},{"time":97112,"text":"Humans and legal persons\nare not synonymous."},{"time":100478,"text":"On the one side,"},{"time":103358,"text":"there have been many human beings\nover the centuries"},{"time":107491,"text":"who have been legal things."},{"time":109464,"text":"Slaves were legal things."},{"time":110997,"text":"Women, children,\nwere sometimes legal things."},{"time":115499,"text":"Indeed, a great deal of civil rights\nstruggle over the last centuries"},{"time":119146,"text":"has been to punch a hole\nthrough that wall and begin to feed"},{"time":123659,"text":"these human things through the wall\nand have them become legal persons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":128713,"text":"But alas, that hole has closed up."},{"time":132772,"text":"Now, on the other side are legal persons,"},{"time":134819,"text":"but they've never only been\nlimited to human beings."},{"time":138952,"text":"There are, for example, there are many\nlegal persons who are not even alive."},{"time":142940,"text":"In the United States,"},{"time":144547,"text":"we're aware of the fact\nthat corporations are legal persons."},{"time":148540,"text":"In pre-independence India,"},{"time":150515,"text":"a court held that a Hindu idol\nwas a legal person,"},{"time":153139,"text":"that a mosque was a legal person."},{"time":155200,"text":"In 2000, the Indian Supreme Court"},{"time":157630,"text":"held that the holy books\nof the Sikh religion was a legal person,"},{"time":161173,"text":"and in 2012, just recently,"},{"time":163472,"text":"there was a treaty between\nthe indigenous peoples of New Zealand"},{"time":167233,"text":"and the crown, in which it was agreed\nthat a river was a legal person"},{"time":170484,"text":"who owned its own riverbed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":173525,"text":"Now, I read Peter Singer's book in 1980,"},{"time":176776,"text":"when I had a full head\nof lush, brown hair,"},{"time":180500,"text":"and indeed I was moved by it,"},{"time":183088,"text":"because I had become a lawyer because\nI wanted to speak for the voiceless,"},{"time":186616,"text":"defend the defenseless,"},{"time":187851,"text":"and I'd never realized how voiceless\nand defenseless the trillions,"},{"time":192263,"text":"billions of nonhuman animals are."},{"time":195769,"text":"And I began to work\nas an animal protection lawyer."},{"time":198788,"text":"And by 1985, I realized that I was trying\nto accomplish something"},{"time":203664,"text":"that was literally impossible,"},{"time":205591,"text":"the reason being that all of my clients,"},{"time":208215,"text":"all the animals whose interests\nI was trying to defend,"},{"time":211697,"text":"were legal things; they were invisible."},{"time":214182,"text":"It was not going to work, so I decided"},{"time":216102,"text":"that the only thing that was going to work\nwas they had, at least some of them,"},{"time":220066,"text":"had to also be moved through a hole\nthat we could open up again in that wall"},{"time":223864,"text":"and begin feeding the appropriate\nnonhuman animals through that hole"},{"time":227440,"text":"onto the other side\nof being legal persons."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230986,"text":"Now, at that time, there was\nvery little known about or spoken about"},{"time":236426,"text":"truly animal rights,"},{"time":238794,"text":"about the idea of having legal personhood\nor legal rights for a nonhuman animal,"},{"time":243235,"text":"and I knew it was going\nto take a long time."},{"time":246005,"text":"And so, in 1985, I figured that it\nwould take about 30 years"},{"time":249405,"text":"before we'd be able to even begin\na strategic litigation,"},{"time":252934,"text":"long-term campaign, in order to be able\nto punch another hole through that wall."},{"time":258716,"text":"It turned out that I was pessimistic,\nthat it only took 28."}]},{"cues":[{"time":266801,"text":"So what we had to do in order\nto begin was not only"},{"time":273240,"text":"to write law review articles\nand teach classes, write books,"},{"time":277922,"text":"but we had to then begin\nto get down to the nuts and bolts"},{"time":280890,"text":"of how you litigate that kind of case."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282875,"text":"So one of the first things we needed to do\nwas figure out what a cause of action was,"},{"time":286908,"text":"a legal cause of action."},{"time":288367,"text":"And a legal cause of action\nis a vehicle that lawyers use"},{"time":291264,"text":"to put their arguments in front of courts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":296840,"text":"It turns out there's\na very interesting case"},{"time":299744,"text":"that had occurred almost 250 years ago\nin London called Somerset vs. Stewart,"},{"time":304348,"text":"whereby a black slave\nhad used the legal system"},{"time":307444,"text":"and had moved from a legal thing\nto a legal person."},{"time":310323,"text":"I was so interested in it that I\neventually wrote an entire book about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":314386,"text":"James Somerset was an eight-year-old boy\nwhen he was kidnapped from West Africa."},{"time":319773,"text":"He survived the Middle Passage,"},{"time":322720,"text":"and he was sold to a Scottish businessman\nnamed Charles Stewart in Virginia."},{"time":327894,"text":"Now, 20 years later, Stewart\nbrought James Somerset to London,"},{"time":332102,"text":"and after he got there, James decided\nhe was going to escape."},{"time":335980,"text":"And so one of the first things he did\nwas to get himself baptized,"},{"time":339620,"text":"because he wanted to get\na set of godparents,"},{"time":341901,"text":"because to an 18th-century slave,"},{"time":343712,"text":"they knew that one of the major\nresponsibilities of godfathers"},{"time":346870,"text":"was to help you escape."}]},{"cues":[{"time":348982,"text":"And so in the fall of 1771,"},{"time":352998,"text":"James Somerset had a confrontation\nwith Charles Stewart."},{"time":355641,"text":"We don't know exactly what happened,\nbut then James dropped out of sight."},{"time":360313,"text":"An enraged Charles Stewart\nthen hired slave catchers"},{"time":363309,"text":"to canvass the city of London,"},{"time":365550,"text":"find him, bring him\nnot back to Charles Stewart,"},{"time":368150,"text":"but to a ship, the Ann and Mary,\nthat was floating in London Harbour,"},{"time":374173,"text":"and he was chained to the deck,"},{"time":375793,"text":"and the ship was to set sail for Jamaica"},{"time":377797,"text":"where James was to be sold\nin the slave markets"},{"time":380816,"text":"and be doomed to the three to five\nyears of life that a slave had"},{"time":384299,"text":"harvesting sugar cane in Jamaica."},{"time":387150,"text":"Well now James' godparents\nswung into action."},{"time":390359,"text":"They approached the most powerful judge,"},{"time":392866,"text":"Lord Mansfield, who was chief judge\nof the court of King's Bench,"},{"time":396512,"text":"and they demanded that he issue\na common law writ of habeus corpus"},{"time":400157,"text":"on behalf of James Somerset."}]},{"cues":[{"time":401991,"text":"Now, the common law is the kind of law\nthat English-speaking judges can make"},{"time":405962,"text":"when they're not cabined in\nby statutes or constitutions,"},{"time":410099,"text":"and a writ of habeus corpus\nis called the Great Writ,"},{"time":412695,"text":"capital G, capital W,"},{"time":414762,"text":"and it's meant to protect any of us\nwho are detained against our will."},{"time":419290,"text":"A writ of habeus corpus is issued."},{"time":421263,"text":"The detainer is required\nto bring the detainee in"},{"time":423701,"text":"and give a legally sufficient reason\nfor depriving him of his bodily liberty."}]},{"cues":[{"time":429576,"text":"Well, Lord Mansfield had to make\na decision right off the bat,"},{"time":434570,"text":"because if James Somerset\nwas a legal thing,"},{"time":437354,"text":"he was not eligible\nfor a writ of habeus corpus,"},{"time":440419,"text":"only if he could be a legal person."},{"time":442439,"text":"So Lord Mansfield decided\nthat he would assume,"},{"time":445457,"text":"without deciding, that James Somerset\nwas indeed a legal person,"},{"time":449560,"text":"and he issued the writ of habeus corpus,\nand James's body was brought in"},{"time":452971,"text":"by the captain of the ship."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454482,"text":"There were a series of hearings\nover the next six months."},{"time":457183,"text":"On June 22, 1772, Lord Mansfield\nsaid that slavery was so odious,"},{"time":463011,"text":"and he used the word \"odious,\""},{"time":464845,"text":"that the common law would not support it,\nand he ordered James free."},{"time":468723,"text":"At that moment, James Somerset\nunderwent a legal transubstantiation."},{"time":472883,"text":"The free man who walked\nout of the courtroom"},{"time":474943,"text":"looked exactly like the slave\nwho had walked in,"},{"time":477191,"text":"but as far as the law was concerned,\nthey had nothing whatsoever in common."}]},{"cues":[{"time":482790,"text":"The next thing we did is that\nthe Nonhuman Rights Project,"},{"time":485740,"text":"which I founded, then began to look at\nwhat kind of values and principles"},{"time":489250,"text":"do we want to put before the judges?"},{"time":492128,"text":"What values and principles\ndid they imbibe with their mother's milk,"},{"time":496007,"text":"were they taught in law school,\ndo they use every day,"},{"time":499090,"text":"do they believe with all their hearts --\nand we chose liberty and equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":502779,"text":"Now, liberty right is the kind of right\nto which you're entitled\n"},{"time":505811,"text":"because of how you're put together,"},{"time":508152,"text":"and a fundamental liberty right\nprotects a fundamental interest."},{"time":513489,"text":"And the supreme interest in the common law"},{"time":516724,"text":"are the rights to autonomy\nand self-determination."},{"time":522015,"text":"So they are so powerful that\nin a common law country,"},{"time":525795,"text":"if you go to a hospital and you refuse\nlife-saving medical treatment,"},{"time":530393,"text":"a judge will not order it forced upon you,"},{"time":532640,"text":"because they will respect\nyour self-determination and your autonomy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":537451,"text":"Now, an equality right is the kind\nof right to which you're entitled"},{"time":540714,"text":"because you resemble someone else\nin a relevant way,"},{"time":543610,"text":"and there's the rub, relevant way."},{"time":545601,"text":"So if you are that, then because\nthey have the right, you're like them,"},{"time":549339,"text":"you're entitled to the right."},{"time":551684,"text":"Now, courts and legislatures\ndraw lines all the time."},{"time":554846,"text":"Some are included, some are excluded."},{"time":557118,"text":"But you have to,\nat the bare minimum you must --"},{"time":563260,"text":"that line has to be a reasonable means\nto a legitimate end."},{"time":567695,"text":"The Nonhuman Rights Project\nargues that drawing a line"},{"time":570435,"text":"in order to enslave an autonomous\nand self-determining being"},{"time":573742,"text":"like you're seeing behind me,"},{"time":575530,"text":"that that's a violation of equality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579270,"text":"We then searched through 80 jurisdictions,"},{"time":581820,"text":"it took us seven years,\nto find the jurisdiction"},{"time":584065,"text":"where we wanted to begin\nfiling our first suit."},{"time":586271,"text":"We chose the state of New York."},{"time":587770,"text":"Then we decided upon\nwho our plaintiffs are going to be."},{"time":590392,"text":"We decided upon chimpanzees,"},{"time":592258,"text":"not just because Jane Goodall\nwas on our board of directors,"},{"time":595109,"text":"but because they, Jane and others,"},{"time":598862,"text":"have studied chimpanzees\nintensively for decades."},{"time":601582,"text":"We know the extraordinary\ncognitive capabilities that they have,"},{"time":605158,"text":"and they also resemble the kind\nthat human beings have."},{"time":608292,"text":"And so we chose chimpanzees,\nand we began to then canvass the world"},{"time":613424,"text":"to find the experts\nin chimpanzee cognition."},{"time":616256,"text":"We found them in Japan, Sweden, Germany,\nScotland, England and the United States,"},{"time":620761,"text":"and amongst them, they wrote\n100 pages of affidavits"},{"time":623524,"text":"in which they set out more than 40 ways"},{"time":626320,"text":"in which their complex\ncognitive capability,"},{"time":629120,"text":"either individually or together,"},{"time":631140,"text":"all added up to autonomy\nand self-determination."}]},{"cues":[{"time":635429,"text":"Now, these included, for example,\nthat they were conscious."},{"time":638936,"text":"But they're also conscious\nthat they're conscious."},{"time":641283,"text":"They know they have a mind.\nThey know that others have minds."},{"time":644139,"text":"They know they're individuals,\nand that they can live."},{"time":646682,"text":"They understand that they lived yesterday\nand they will live tomorrow."},{"time":649975,"text":"They engage in mental time travel.\nThey remember what happened yesterday."},{"time":653419,"text":"They can anticipate tomorrow,"},{"time":654870,"text":"which is why it's so terrible to imprison\na chimpanzee, especially alone."},{"time":659587,"text":"It's the thing that we do\nto our worst criminals,"},{"time":662184,"text":"and we do that to chimpanzees\nwithout even thinking about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":667715,"text":"They have some kind of moral capacity."},{"time":670426,"text":"When they play economic games\nwith human beings,"},{"time":673352,"text":"they'll spontaneously make fair offers,\neven when they're not required to do so."},{"time":677392,"text":"They are numerate.\nThey understand numbers."},{"time":679425,"text":"They can do some simple math."},{"time":680805,"text":"They can engage in language --\nor to stay out of the language wars,"},{"time":684869,"text":"they're involved in intentional\nand referential communication"},{"time":688234,"text":"in which they pay attention\nto the attitudes of those"},{"time":690721,"text":"with whom they are speaking."},{"time":692252,"text":"They have culture."},{"time":693900,"text":"They have a material culture,\na social culture."},{"time":696501,"text":"They have a symbolic culture."},{"time":698916,"text":"Scientists in the Taï Forests\nin the Ivory Coast"},{"time":702817,"text":"found chimpanzees who were using\nthese rocks to smash open"},{"time":706346,"text":"the incredibly hard hulls of nuts."},{"time":709132,"text":"It takes a long time\nto learn how to do that,"},{"time":711431,"text":"and they excavated the area\nand they found"},{"time":713544,"text":"that this material culture,\nthis way of doing it,"},{"time":716377,"text":"these rocks, had passed down\nfor at least 4,300 years"},{"time":719720,"text":"through 225 chimpanzee generations."}]},{"cues":[{"time":724712,"text":"So now we needed to find our chimpanzee."},{"time":727104,"text":"Our chimpanzee,"},{"time":730284,"text":"first we found two of them\nin the state of New York."},{"time":733187,"text":"Both of them would die before\nwe could even get our suits filed."},{"time":736391,"text":"Then we found Tommy."},{"time":738272,"text":"Tommy is a chimpanzee.\nYou see him behind me."},{"time":741384,"text":"Tommy was a chimpanzee.\nWe found him in that cage."},{"time":743891,"text":"We found him in a small room\nthat was filled with cages"},{"time":747351,"text":"in a larger warehouse structure on a used\ntrailer lot in central New York."},{"time":752537,"text":"We found Kiko, who is partially deaf."},{"time":754711,"text":"Kiko was in the back of a cement\nstorefront in western Massachusetts."},{"time":760353,"text":"And we found Hercules and Leo."},{"time":762250,"text":"They're two young male chimpanzees"},{"time":763953,"text":"who are being used for biomedical,\nanatomical research at Stony Brook."},{"time":767366,"text":"We found them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":768671,"text":"And so on the last week of December 2013,"},{"time":771383,"text":"the Nonhuman Rights Project filed three\nsuits all across the state of New York"},{"time":775323,"text":"using the same common law\nwrit of habeus corpus argument"},{"time":778801,"text":"that had been used with James Somerset,"},{"time":781529,"text":"and we demanded that the judges issue\nthese common law writs of habeus corpus."},{"time":786616,"text":"We wanted the chimpanzees out,"},{"time":788727,"text":"and we wanted them brought\nto Save the Chimps,"},{"time":791513,"text":"a tremendous chimpanzee\nsanctuary in South Florida"},{"time":795461,"text":"which involves an artificial lake\nwith 12 or 13 islands --"},{"time":800548,"text":"there are two or three acres\nwhere two dozen chimpanzees live"},{"time":803411,"text":"on each of them."},{"time":804571,"text":"And these chimpanzees would then live\nthe life of a chimpanzee,"},{"time":807521,"text":"with other chimpanzees in an environment\nthat was as close to Africa as possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":811923,"text":"Now, all these cases are still going on."},{"time":816820,"text":"We have not yet run into\nour Lord Mansfield."},{"time":820622,"text":"We shall. We shall."},{"time":822230,"text":"This is a long-term strategic\nlitigation campaign. We shall."},{"time":826110,"text":"And to quote Winston Churchill,"},{"time":828225,"text":"the way we view our cases\nis that they're not the end,"},{"time":832393,"text":"they're not even the beginning of the end,"},{"time":834436,"text":"but they are perhaps\nthe end of the beginning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838580,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":840497,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}